        "content": "import heapq\nimport math\n\n\ndef a_star(graph, start, goal, heuristic):\n    '''\n    A* shortest-path search.\n\n    Inputs:\n    [graph]: adjacency mapping of the form {node: {neighbor: weight, ...}}\n             with non-negative numeric edge weights\n    [start]: source node, must appear as a key of [graph]\n    [goal]:  target node\n    [heuristic]: callable taking a node and returning a numeric\n                 estimate of the remaining distance to [goal].\n                 For optimality the heuristic must be admissible\n                 (never overestimates the true remaining distance).\n\n    Outputs:\n    [path]: list of nodes from [start] to [goal] along the shortest\n            path. Empty list if [goal] is unreachable from [start].\n    [length]: total length of the shortest path. math.inf if [goal]\n              is unreachable from [start].\n    '''\n\n    g_score = {start: 0}\n    came_from = {}\n    # counter breaks f-score ties so the heap never compares nodes directly\n    counter = 0\n    open_heap = [(heuristic(start), counter, start)]\n    closed = set()\n\n    while open_heap:\n        _, _, current = heapq.heappop(open_heap)\n\n        if current == goal:\n            path = [current]\n            while path[-1] in came_from:\n                path.append(came_from[path[-1]])\n            path.reverse()\n            return path, g_score[goal]\n\n        if current in closed:\n            continue\n        closed.add(current)\n\n        for neighbor, weight in graph.get(current, {}).items():\n            tentative_g = g_score[current] + weight\n            if tentative_g < g_score.get(neighbor, math.inf):\n                came_from[neighbor] = current\n                g_score[neighbor] = tentative_g\n                counter += 1\n                heapq.heappush(\n                    open_heap,\n                    (tentative_g + heuristic(neighbor), counter, neighbor),\n                )\n\n    return [], math.inf\n",
